page.title: 09RECREATION.
page.content:
A Walk Round the Country Park.
Our family went for a walk in the Country Park. Helen and Alison fed the ducks while I made a list of the different kind of ducks for a project I was doing. We walked along the path where we found some rabbits and a caterpillar. We came back along a path where the fishermen fish from the bank of the lake. We saw another rabbit which hopped into the undergrowth. We saw some people boating on the lake. While we were walking through the woodland we saw an animal which looked like a mole and a grey squirrel which ran up a tree. We then went to our car in the car park and rode home.
